\nTwo British-flag vessels were offered for three-month charter to the Chinese Communists\nThe vessels would operate between Japan and the Chinese mainland.\n\nComment: The British Government has been unwilling to follow the US and Panamanian lead in barring its merchant ships from the China trade. Accordingly, British-flag ships, many operating under charter to the Chinese or to the East European Satellites, have been more active in this trade than those of any other registry.\n\nLast October a London firm asked its Hong Kong correspondent to investigate the advantages of putting additional British ships on the China run, in view of the reported loss of tonnage resulting from the withdrawal of Panamanian ships", "token_count": 121, "token_end_0based": 123, "token_start_0based": 3, "token_text": "two british-flag vessels offered for charter to chinese communists two british-flag vessels were offered for three-month charter to the chinese communists the vessels would operate between japan and the chinese mainland comment the british government has been unwilling to follow the us and panamanian lead in barring its merchant ships from the china trade accordingly british-flag ships many operating under charter to the chinese or to the east european satellites have been more active in this trade than those of any other registry last october a london firm asked its hong kong correspondent to investigate the advantages of putting additional british ships on the china run in view of the reported loss of tonnage resulting from the withdrawal of panamanian ships", "unred_source_page": 3}
